I think the fact only fedora 22 is using dnf is probably true today. What about fedora 23? Incoming Red Hat? Therefore I would instead check if dnf exists, or if yum exists. I would suggest something like this instead.

 if dnf --version; then
   YUM=${YUM:-dnf}
 elif yum --version; then
   YUM=${YUM:-dnf}
 fi

